      "link": "https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:activity:7444752687247634432?commentUrn=urn%3Ali%3Acomment%3A%28activity%3A7444752687247634432%2C7448118543730003968%29&dashCommentUrn=urn%3Ali%3Afsd_comment%3A%287448118543730003968%2Curn%3Ali%3Aactivity%3A7444752687247634432%29",
      "text": "Thank you Gergely Orosz. The copyright angle is very interesting but the one more question is what this means for agent security architecture. System prompts, permission layers, feature flags — all now public. Any agent that relies on obscurity for its security boundaries just lost that layer permanently. The takeaway for anyone building agents: assume your internals will be exposed. Design permission scoping and blast radius containment as if every line of your agent code is already on GitHub.",
