      "link": "https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:activity:7444752687247634432?commentUrn=urn%3Ali%3Acomment%3A%28activity%3A7444752687247634432%2C7447642503148724224%29&dashCommentUrn=urn%3Ali%3Afsd_comment%3A%287447642503148724224%2Curn%3Ali%3Aactivity%3A7444752687247634432%29",
      "text": "Nobody created a legit reverse engineered work.  To do that you must only use complied third party set of documents defining the standards, interfaces that are then used by someone that has not seen the original source code. \n\nThat Python and Rust are not clean implementations and would never survive a legal challenge.  They had the source code and told Claude to reimplement in said new language.  That fails on every definition of reverse engineering.  ",
