    {
      "time": 1775594216120,
      "link": "https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:activity:7444752687247634432?commentUrn=urn%3Ali%3Acomment%3A%28activity%3A7444752687247634432%2C7447381923045289985%29&dashCommentUrn=urn%3Ali%3Afsd_comment%3A%287447381923045289985%2Curn%3Ali%3Aactivity%3A7444752687247634432%29",
      "text": "The deeper implication here is for every company shipping proprietary algorithms. If an AI agent can rewrite a codebase across languages in hours, the moat was never the code — it was the data, the domain expertise encoded in architectural decisions, and the institutional knowledge of why certain tradeoffs were made. The Python port preserves syntax but loses context. That gap is where defensibility actually lives.",
